messages.message:
the ibdev-backend template uses a fresh mysql db by default - this was also described in Matt’s tech talk (https://instabase.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENG/pages/2656337921/Schedule+and+Recordings) last Monday

Udit’s sandbox is using traffic interception and thus uses the crafting-aihub.instabase.com (http://crafting-aihub.instabase.com) db
